<title>CANADA: Ottawa invests C$1.8 mln in CAL.</title>
<headline>Ottawa invests C$1.8 mln in CAL.</headline>
<dateline>OTTAWA 1997-03-26</dateline>
<text>
<p>Canada's federal industry minister said on Wednesday that the Canadian government will invest C$1.8 million in Ottawa's CAL Corp, a division of Electromagnetic Sciences Inc of Atlanta.</p>
<p>Minister John Manley said the investment is to be repaid gradually through royalties from the company's CALTRAC star sensing technology, which tracks a space craft's position in space.</p>
<p>The investment is part of the government's Technology Partnerships Canada program to promote high-tech growth.</p>
<p>The investement is expected to create 32 immediate jobs.</p>
<p>((Reuters Ottawa Bureau 613 235-6745))</p>
